      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "On a chopping board, peel and finely chop the onions, garlic and carrots, then trim and finely chop the celery."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Pick and finely chop the rosemary leaves, then finely slice the bacon or pancetta."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Put a large saucepan on a medium-high heat and add 1 tablespoon of olive oil."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the bacon, rosemary, garlic and veg, then cook with the lid ajar for 10 to 15 minutes, or until softened and just turning golden, stirring occasionally."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Stir in the mince, turn the heat up to high and cook for 5 to 10 minutes, or until browned all over,stirring and breaking it up with a spoon as you go."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the tomatoes, tomato purée, vinegar and bay leaves."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Fill and boil the kettle. Then crumble in the stock cube and pour in 400ml boiling water."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Stir well, turn the heat up to high and bring to the boil."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Season with pepper, reduce to a low heat, then cover and simmer for around 1 hour, stirring occasionally."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Remove the lid and continue cooking for 15 to 20 minutes, or until thickened and reduced. Meanwhile...Re-fill and boil the kettle."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Carefully fill a large pot three quarters of the way up with boiling water, add a tiny pinch of salt and bring back to the boil."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the spaghetti and cook according to packet instructions – you want to cook your pasta until it is al dente. This translates as ‘to the tooth’ and means that it should be soft enough to eat, but still have a bit of a bite and firmness to it. Use the timings on the packet instructions as a guide, but try some just before the time is up to make sure it’s perfectly cooked."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Using a microplane, finely grate the Parmesan cheese."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Once the spaghetti is done, ladle out and reserve a cup of cooking water and keep it to one side, then drain in a colander over the sink."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Taste the Bolognese sauce and season with a little more pepper or vinegar, if you think it needs it. Carefully pick out and discard the bay leaves."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Put half the sauce into a container, leave to cool, then freeze for another day."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Stir the spaghetti into the remaining sauce, adding a splash of pasta water to loosen, if needed."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Divide between bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (if using), then serve."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Sauce won't cling to the pasta",
              "cause": "Pasta drained too thoroughly, or sauce too thin.",
              "fix": "Reserve a ladle of starchy cooking water before draining. Toss it through with the pasta and sauce in the pan over heat — the starch binds everything."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Pasta is gummy",
              "cause": "Overcooked, or sat in water after draining.",
              "fix": "Cook a minute less than the packet says, drain, and finish in the sauce. Time it so the pasta meets the sauce in the pan, not the colander."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Cheese clumps when stirred in",
              "cause": "Pan too hot, or cheese added all at once.",
              "fix": "Lower the heat first. Add the cheese a small handful at a time, stirring continuously, with a splash of pasta water to keep the sauce loose."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Sauce tastes sharp or thin",
              "cause": "Tomato or wine hasn't cooked down long enough.",
              "fix": "Give the sauce another ten to fifteen minutes at a low simmer. A pinch of sugar softens an acidic tomato base."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Vegetarian: drop the meat and add 200 g mushrooms (chestnut or porcini) sautéed until they squeak."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Lighter sauce: replace cream with crème fraîche stirred in off the heat — same richness, less weight."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The sauce reheats well the next day; cook the pasta fresh."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The dish sits in the Italian home-cooking tradition: a few good ingredients, a long unhurried cook, and a pan that has fed the family for years. Worth keeping its roots in mind when you taste — the silence between flavours is part of the design."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
